# Redesigned settings page

As CSA Admin has grown over the years, the [settings page](/settings) had gradually become a very dense place, with more and more options added whenever new features were introduced. It was time to rethink it properly.

The settings page has therefore been completely restructured. Instead of one long form, settings are now grouped into clearer sections, each with its own dedicated edit page. The goal is to make it easier to understand what each setting does, find the right option faster, and safely change only the part you are working on.

Several optional features are now also managed more explicitly:

- Annual fee
- Member information page
- SEPA direct debit
- Shares
- VAT

These features can now be activated or deactivated from their own settings section, making the configuration clearer and reducing the number of irrelevant options shown when a feature is not used.

## Better visibility for admins

Because the settings page is no longer just one big edit form, it is now available to all admins in read-only mode.

This means admins can now see the main [settings overview](/settings), including which optional features are available or active, without needing super admin access. Editing settings remains restricted to super admins, and some more advanced details are still only visible inside the edit forms.

All existing configurations have been preserved automatically, so there should be nothing to reconfigure on your side.

Given the scope of this restructuring, please [let me know](/support) if you cannot find a setting anymore, if something feels unclear, or if you notice anything unusual. Thanks!
